Barack Obama Receives Nobel Peace Prize as Fourth US President
American President Barack Obama comes to Oslo, Norway for 26 hours to receive the Nobel Peace Prize as the fourth President of the United States in history.
In addition, he receives the diploma, the medal and a cheque of 1.4 million dollars for his extraordinary efforts to intensify world diplomacy and cooperation among the peoples.
The head of the White House arrives tomorrow together with his wife Michelle in the north-urban metropolis and will be busy all the time.
First, he pays a visit to the Nobel Institute, where he meets for the first time with the five committee members who elected him in October from 172 people and 33 organisations.
The presidents then planned a meeting with the Norwegian King Harald V and Queen Sonja.
In the afternoon, the visit reaches its climax with the ceremony at which Obama takes over the prestigious prize.
He receives the award as the fourth US President, but only as the third to receive the prize directly in office.
The White House has already said that Obama will talk about the war in Afghanistan when the prize is accepted.
The President does not want to avoid this issue because he knows that he is taking over the prize as a president who is currently at war in two countries.
He stepped up the war effort a few days ago by sending more troops to Afghanistan, which none of his critics forgets to highlight.
At the ceremony, Obama also received the Gol Medal, the diploma and the cheque for ten million Swedish crowns (approx. 24 million Czech crowns).
He intends to donate the money for charitable purposes, but he has not yet decided on a concrete charitable work.
The event programme will then include a banquet with the President and his wife, where besides Norway's king and queen, the Prime Minister and another 250 invited guests will be present.
Obama was very cautious about the price from the beginning.
For example, he pointed out that he felt that he didn't deserve the prize.
He also repeated several times that the price is not only for him, but for all those who aspire to the same values as him.
Immediately after the announcement, he stated that this was "an invitation to act" for him.
