Loud, malicious voices roar out of walls and radio.
He can't stand them anymore, the voices that insult and insult him.
Henning T. pulls two cables out of the stereo system, knots them into a loop and attaches them to a hook on the ceiling.
He climbs on a loudspeaker and lays the noose around his neck.
Jump.
The noose's loosening.
This should be a lesson for you, screaming the voices in drum-flailing chorus, "Go to the clinic and let yourself be healed!"
