CNMV has also announced that this offer is aimed at the acquisition of 550,008 shares of Federico Paternina at a price of EUR 7.65 per share, which in turn is 8.95% of the company's capital, which consists of EUR 6,142,786 in shares admitted to the Madrid and Bilbao Stock Exchanges.
In addition, it has been announced that 5,592,778 million shares have been fixed, which cannot be transferred in any way until the closing of the tender and whose price has been fixed by Federico Paternina in accordance with the final laws.
New vehicle assessment programmes
In these days of storms and accidents not only the automotive workshops deserve
Every day, thousands of vehicles involved in an accident are dragged to the workshops, where an expert must assess the damage caused and the cost of the repair.
Not a single accident is the same and calculating the cost of parts and hours of work can be a lengthy and complicated task.
The calculation of repair costs of between 20,000 and 30,000 euros by hand, including parts and working hours, can take up to two or three hours.
On the other hand, with the support of the latest computer tools, it is a matter of minutes
That is why almost 100% of experts use this type of system.
Service and application providers for the assessment of accidents and repairs shall collect the information they receive from manufacturers in order to process it afterwards and to offer it to their customers in the form of a useful programme.
In Spain, Audatex, part of the American group Solera, is the market leader; 80% of all reports are produced with their products.
The other two companies competing with in the tool market for review and preparation of a report are GtMotive and Eurotax.
Working with the data provided by the manufacturers is far from easy.
According to Eduardo Velázquez, Sales Manager of Audatex, 63 manufacturers and importers are working together, each of them providing the information in a different format.
In addition, the amount of data to be processed is becoming larger and larger, up to the point that in the last five years even more versions, variants and motorizations have come on the market than in the entire fifteen years before.
As soon as a new car comes onto the market, work begins for the companies.
It is a tedious task, because each one of the thousands of vehicle parts has to be catagolized and its price entered.
In addition, each model creates a "smart" graphic image, on which you can "click" different parts of the vehicle.
If this is a much-sold model, the work can be completed within a week if the procedure is proceeding rapidly.
If this is a less common car, it can take up to three or four months. Currently, Audatex has complete information on 99.2% of the cars sold in Spain.
Among the more exclusive models, they have information about the Porsche models, but not about Ferrari or Lamborghini.
With regard to the vehicle park on the roads, it is more than 99%.
In order to carry out the documentation work and the production of databases, Audatex has eight centres worldwide (Spain, France, Germany, the USA, Brazil, Mexico, China and Japan) and each of them specializes in certain brands.
The national headquarters are located in Alcobendas (Madrid).
There, more than a hundred technicians (usually mechanics specialists) work simultaneously with three computer screens.
Audatex annually invests 90 million euros in the development of these databases.
Every month they record 2.5 million data and their customers get updates every other day.
The development of this enormous flow of information enables companies to use it in various ways and thus offer different products.
The most common use is the use for repairs and repairs, but depending on the country there are also tools for managing scrap parts or for calculating the filing or residual value of a car.
The only company that informs about a guide about the value of used cars in Spain is Eurotax.
Audatex does not offer this offer in Spain, but in the United States.
When looking through the products that Audatex offers, it is easy to get an overview of the kind of support it provides to industry experts.
This company offers ten different tools, with the star of the products AudaPlus, a standard solution for the assessment of accidents for the reviewers.
It includes vehicles, motorcycles and light and heavy industrial vehicles.
In addition to the cost of the parts, it contains the repair times estimated by the manufacturer or the painting prices.
This tool is paid for according to the intended use, i.e. for each expert opinion.
Most expensive it will be for customers who use it rarely, maximum ten times a month, namely 5.75 euros per month.
In contrast, any insurance company that makes thousands of reports negotiates the price with Audatex.
With other products, such as AudaVIN, you can fully identify a vehicle and the equipment with which it ran off the assembly line, solely by means of the chassis number.
AudaGlass deals with the car discs, and AudaSubastas is an internet service open to the specialist market, which can be offered for vehicles that have been declared total damage.
Your statistical service is very useful in identifying trends, conducting geodemographic analyses or in obtaining information on trade mark and model deviations.
One can, for example, examine how many models of a particular car brand had to go to the workshop due to breakdowns or how many of them were involved in a serious accident during a certain period of time.
Gt Motive is the only Spanish company dedicated to the development of this type of computer tools.
It sells, among other things, Gt Estimate, which is also intended for reviewers and provides digital images in the same way, access to parts or prices and official working hours of the manufacturer.
Gt Motive is a company of the Group Einsa, which was founded in 1971 as a provider of services and solutions for the assessment of damage, breakdown or maintenance of vehicles.
The GT Expert Review Guide is a reference product on the market.
They work with 24,000 users in workshops, 3,100 reviewers and 53 insurance companies.
Their business volume has increased by 20% per year over the last three years and sales amounted to 10.8 million euros in 2008.
