Cost estimate of the workshop in four steps
With the Auda-Taller tool, the company Audatex ensures that the user receives a cost estimate in just four steps: identification of the vehicle, search of the spare part, creation and creation of a cost estimate.
Easy handling of these systems is a fundamental condition, especially to convince older professionals who are usually more or less opposed to the use of these new computer techniques.
The database includes 1,034 vehicles, 666 of which are passenger cars, 109 off-road vehicles, 137 motorcycles, 78 vans and 44 trucks.
Of course, you need a computer with Internet connection for use.
After the model to be repaired has been identified by the chassis number, a graphic of the respective model appears and then the required spare part is selected.
The user can include variables such as the price of working hours, surcharges or discounts, and then he can print out the estimate and pass it on to his customer.
However, AudaTaller is not a tool for evaluation like AudaPlus, but rather a reference catalogue.
The main difference between the two systems is that the workshop-oriented system does not include estimated working hours.
The cost of using this tool is 350 euros a year, an amount that the customer can easily pay for.
Audatex is currently working on offering these images in three-dimensional format.
This is an innovation that auto mechanics have been waiting for for for a long time, for example, because they can choose a door and then turn the picture completely to look at the inside.
